  Locus:
    Page: 85
    Verse: 13
Tags:
  - Death
---
Death is but a new birth into a new state. Death is not to be feared, any
more than birth. When the body ceases to be, the spirit emerges, free and
unencumbered. I shall be richer all my life for this sorrow.
